other_tests.findings: Hyperemic and enlarged retrocecal appendix up to 12 mm containing fluid and a few foci of air; inflammation associated with a small amount of fluid in the right inferior edge of the peritoneal cavity and mild thickening of adjacent fascial planes.
No overt evidence of abscess formation or perforation; liver demonstrates trace perifalciform fatty infiltration; retrocecal appendix is hyperemic and enlarged, with inflammation and fluid.
